<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>智能新闻| smithsonianmag.com</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/rss/smart-news/</link><description>智能新闻的 RSS 提要</description><lastBuildDate>Tue, 14 Jul 2026 13:03:06 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>古罗马人相信守护神。考古学家刚刚在英格兰北部发现了一个具有 1,600 年历史的罕见雕刻</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/romans-put-their-faith-in-guardian-spirits-archaeologists-just-found-a-rare-1600-year-old-carving-of-one-in-northern-england-180989118/</link><description>被称为“天才”的保护神或神被认为可以为特定的人、家庭或地方带来好运和繁荣。考古学家在罗马时期的英国并没有发现很多关于他们的描述</description><pubDate>Tue, 14 Jul 2026 11:45:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/romans-put-their-faith-in-guardian-spirits-archaeologists-just-found-a-rare-1600-year-old-carving-of-one-in-northern-england-180989118/</guid></item><item><title>托马斯·杰斐逊的《独立宣言》原始草稿现在可以在国会图书馆看到</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/thomas-jeffersons-original-rough-draft-of-the-declaration-of-independence-can-be-seen-at-library-of-congress-180989113/</link><description>新展览展示了该文件的编辑方式，还展示了葛底斯堡演说的早期副本</description><pubDate>Tue, 14 Jul 2026 11:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/thomas-jeffersons-original-rough-draft-of-the-declaration-of-independence-can-be-seen-at-library-of-congress-180989113/</guid></item><item><title>这块霸王龙化石的拍卖价格可能是有史以来拍卖价格最高的恐龙。科学家担心他们会失去研究它的机会</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-t-rex-fossil-could-fetch-the-largest-sum-of-any-dinosaur-ever-auctioned-scientists-worry-theyll-lose-the-chance-to-study-it-180989114/</link><description>“Gus”的起价为 1900 万美元，这对于公共机构来说是一个很高的价格。研究人员检查私人收藏的标本可能更困难，而且它们实际上不可能包含在顶级科学期刊的研究中</description><pubDate>Mon, 13 Jul 2026 20:13:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-t-rex-fossil-could-fetch-the-largest-sum-of-any-dinosaur-ever-auctioned-scientists-worry-theyll-lose-the-chance-to-study-it-180989114/</guid></item><item><title>世界上最大的运营蒸汽机车重达 120 万磅。现在，历史悠久的火车可能会驶向您的城镇</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-largest-operating-steam-locomotive-in-the-world-weighs-1-2-million-pounds-now-the-historic-train-may-be-coming-to-your-town-180989112/</link><description>Big Boy No. 4014 建于 20 世纪 40 年代，在行驶超过 100 万英里后于 1961 年退役。现在它正在全国范围内庆祝美国诞辰 250 周年</description><pubDate>Mon, 13 Jul 2026 17:26:51 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-largest-operating-steam-locomotive-in-the-world-weighs-1-2-million-pounds-now-the-historic-train-may-be-coming-to-your-town-180989112/</guid></item><item><title>世界卫生组织警告称，到 2050 年，癌症病例预计将增加近一倍。低收入国家将受到不成比例的影响</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/cancer-cases-are-expected-to-nearly-double-by-2050-warns-the-who-low-income-countries-will-be-disproportionately-affected-180989102/</link><description>世界卫生组织在一份新报告中预测，到 2050 年，每年新增确诊病例将从目前的约 2060 万增加到近 3500 万。增幅最大的地区将是非洲和东地中海地区</description><pubDate>Mon, 13 Jul 2026 15:44:42 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/cancer-cases-are-expected-to-nearly-double-by-2050-warns-the-who-low-income-countries-will-be-disproportionately-affected-180989102/</guid></item><item><title>今年北美太平洋沿岸发现近150头灰鲸死亡，科学家敲响了警钟</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/nearly-150-gray-whales-have-been-found-dead-along-north-americas-pacific-shore-this-year-prompting-scientists-to-sound-the-alarm-180989109/</link><description>每年沿着西海岸在北极和墨西哥之间迁徙的东部灰鲸的数量近年来一直在下降。环保人士表示，2026 年可能是有记录以来海洋哺乳动物死亡人数最多的一年</description><pubDate>Mon, 13 Jul 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/nearly-150-gray-whales-have-been-found-dead-along-north-americas-pacific-shore-this-year-prompting-scientists-to-sound-the-alarm-180989109/</guid></item><item><title>几千年前，两只狼是如何来到这个偏远岛屿的？研究人员认为人类将它们带到那里，然后照顾它们</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/how-did-two-wolves-end-up-on-this-remote-island-thousands-of-years-ago-researchers-think-humans-brought-them-there-then-cared-for-them-180989110/</link><description>这一发现表明，在驯养狗出现很久之后，人类可能仍与狼保持着关系</description><pubDate>Mon, 13 Jul 2026 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/how-did-two-wolves-end-up-on-this-remote-island-thousands-of-years-ago-researchers-think-humans-brought-them-there-then-cared-for-them-180989110/</guid></item><item><title>参观考古学家在这座埋藏在埃及绿洲中、拥有 1600 年历史的拜占庭基督教小镇中发现的文物</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-artifacts-that-archaeologists-discovered-in-this-1600-year-old-byzantine-christian-town-buried-in-an-oasis-in-egypt-180989106/</link><description>这个泥砖村庄拥有街道、塔楼和一座大教堂。研究人员出土了日常用品，如谷物研磨机、烤箱和约 200 个陶片——写在破碎陶器上的古代收据和笔记</description><pubDate>Fri, 10 Jul 2026 20:07:04 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-artifacts-that-archaeologists-discovered-in-this-1600-year-old-byzantine-christian-town-buried-in-an-oasis-in-egypt-180989106/</guid></item><item><title>在美国，可导致腹泻数周的寄生虫感染病例迅速增加，以下是您需要了解的内容</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/cases-of-a-parasitic-infection-that-can-cause-diarrhea-for-weeks-are-rapidly-rising-in-the-us-heres-what-to-know-180989108/</link><description>这种疾病是由微小寄生虫卡耶塔环孢子虫引起的，它通过被粪便污染的食物或水传播，通常在农场。卫生官员仍在调查多州疫情的来源</description><pubDate>Fri, 10 Jul 2026 19:26:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/cases-of-a-parasitic-infection-that-can-cause-diarrhea-for-weeks-are-rapidly-rising-in-the-us-heres-what-to-know-180989108/</guid></item><item><title>在最近的一次无耻抢劫中，价值 500 万美元的珠宝和艺术品从法国著名设计师博物馆被盗</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-the-latest-brazen-heist-jewelry-and-artworks-worth-5-million-were-stolen-from-famed-french-designer-lalique-museum-180989105/</link><description>三名窃贼从法国东部的莱俪博物馆偷走了 27 件藏品，其中包括一件蜻蜓吊坠</description><pubDate>Fri, 10 Jul 2026 17:57:03 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-the-latest-brazen-heist-jewelry-and-artworks-worth-5-million-were-stolen-from-famed-french-designer-lalique-museum-180989105/</guid></item><item><title>大黄蜂在吃完甜食后似乎会“舔嘴唇”，在尝到不好的味道时会摇头，暗示了昆虫的内心生活</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/bumblebees-seem-to-lick-their-lips-after-sweet-treats-and-shake-their-heads-at-bad-tastes-hinting-at-the-insects-inner-lives-180989098/</link><description>慢动作视频表明，昆虫在喜欢或不喜欢零食时会表现出不同的行为。这些发现可能提供一种研究他们的情绪状态的新方法</description><pubDate>Fri, 10 Jul 2026 15:45:42 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/bumblebees-seem-to-lick-their-lips-after-sweet-treats-and-shake-their-heads-at-bad-tastes-hinting-at-the-insects-inner-lives-180989098/</guid></item><item><title>大约 10 万年前，这个人脸部被刺伤，但幸存下来。他可能是第一批已知的锋利武器袭击受害者之一</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/roughly-100000-years-ago-this-man-got-stabbed-in-the-face-and-survived-hes-likely-one-of-the-first-known-victims-of-an-attack-by-a-sharp-weapon-180989103/</link><description>研究人员对卡夫泽洞穴中发现的一具年轻成年男性遗骸进行了调查，称伤势随着时间的推移而愈合，这意味着受害者的社区可能照顾过他</description><pubDate>Fri, 10 Jul 2026 13:53:24 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/roughly-100000-years-ago-this-man-got-stabbed-in-the-face-and-survived-hes-likely-one-of-the-first-known-victims-of-an-attack-by-a-sharp-weapon-180989103/</guid></item><item><title>科学家称，南澳大利亚致命藻华背后的罪魁祸首可能是迄今为止测试过的毒性最强的物种</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-culprit-behind-south-australias-deadly-algal-bloom-might-be-the-most-toxic-species-ever-tested-scientists-say-180989100/</link><description>卡伦藻是一种罕见的微小藻类，它产生的毒素会损害神经细胞，在极低浓度下即可致命</description><pubDate>Fri, 10 Jul 2026 12:46:29 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-culprit-behind-south-australias-deadly-algal-bloom-might-be-the-most-toxic-species-ever-tested-scientists-say-180989100/</guid></item><item><title>驼鹿是科罗拉多州本地人还是引进的外来者？新研究表明这些动物已经在该州生活了几个世纪</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/are-moose-colorado-natives-or-introduced-outsiders-new-research-suggests-that-the-animals-have-lived-in-the-state-for-centuries-180989091/</link><description>官员们表示，驼鹿直到 20 世纪 70 年代末才被引入该州。但历史文献和考古证据表明，他们早在那之前就居住在那里</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 Jul 2026 20:15:43 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/are-moose-colorado-natives-or-introduced-outsiders-new-research-suggests-that-the-animals-have-lived-in-the-state-for-centuries-180989091/</guid></item><item><title>乡村音乐传奇人物多莉·帕顿的自传音乐剧《探索她从田纳西州东部出发的旅程》将于今年冬天在百老汇上演</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/country-music-legend-dolly-partons-autobiographical-musical-exploring-her-journey-from-east-tennessee-will-hit-broadway-this-winter-180989099/</link><description>《多莉：真正的原创音乐剧》去年在帕顿的家乡纳什维尔首演</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 Jul 2026 19:27:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/country-music-legend-dolly-partons-autobiographical-musical-exploring-her-journey-from-east-tennessee-will-hit-broadway-this-winter-180989099/</guid></item><item><title>我们可以通过人为改变气候来缓解超级厄尔尼诺现象吗？一项新研究表明是的</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/could-we-mitigate-super-el-ninos-by-artificially-changing-the-climate-a-new-study-indicates-yes-180989101/</link><description>研究人员使用计算机模型来观察，如果科学家在过去强烈的厄尔尼诺现象面前使海洋云变亮，会发生什么</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 Jul 2026 18:17:32 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/could-we-mitigate-super-el-ninos-by-artificially-changing-the-climate-a-new-study-indicates-yes-180989101/</guid></item><item><title>为什么荷兰博物馆的地板上铺满了 800 磅重的奶油花生酱？</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/why-did-this-dutch-museum-cover-the-floor-with-an-800-pound-installation-of-creamy-peanut-butter-180989097/</link><description>“Pindakaasvloer”或“花生酱地板”突显了艺术家 Wim T. Schippers 上个月去世前在其艺术作品中捕捉到的荒谬幽默感</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 Jul 2026 18:15:35 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/why-did-this-dutch-museum-cover-the-floor-with-an-800-pound-installation-of-creamy-peanut-butter-180989097/</guid></item><item><title>科学家刚刚获悉这只蝙蝠在飞行途中吃掉鸟类。文艺复兴时期的画家可能在数百年前就知道了它</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientists-just-learned-that-this-bat-eats-birds-midflight-a-renaissance-painter-may-have-known-about-it-hundreds-of-years-ago-180989096/</link><description>去年秋天，科学家报告了首次已知的大型夜蛾在夜间飞行时捕猎和捕食鸣禽的记录。但老扬·勃鲁盖尔 (Jan Brueghel the Elder) 的一幅 17 世纪艺术作品似乎描绘了该物种嘴里叼着带羽毛的猎物飞行</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 Jul 2026 16:17:58 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientists-just-learned-that-this-bat-eats-birds-midflight-a-renaissance-painter-may-have-known-about-it-hundreds-of-years-ago-180989096/</guid></item><item><title>古代DNA表明，哈萨克斯坦铁器时代的“金人”和欧亚大陆的其他精英斯基泰人继承了他们的崇高社会地位</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/kazakhstans-iron-age-golden-man-and-other-elite-scythians-of-eurasia-inherited-their-high-social-status-ancient-dna-suggests-180989089/</link><description>研究人员长期以来一直想知道古代游牧武士的上层成员是否通过个人成就或与生俱来的权利获得了社会地位</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 Jul 2026 16:04:08 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/kazakhstans-iron-age-golden-man-and-other-elite-scythians-of-eurasia-inherited-their-high-social-status-ancient-dna-suggests-180989089/</guid></item><item><title>新研究表明，英国医生用来给患者接种的天花痂可能是将这种致命疾病引入澳大利亚的</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/smallpox-scabs-that-british-doctors-used-to-inoculate-patients-may-have-introduced-the-deadly-disease-to-australia-new-research-suggests-180989093/</link><description>两项新研究发现，18 世纪末乘船抵达的英国殖民者可能引入了天花，对原住民社区的破坏程度远超之前所知</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 Jul 2026 14:14:36 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/smallpox-scabs-that-british-doctors-used-to-inoculate-patients-may-have-introduced-the-deadly-disease-to-australia-new-research-suggests-180989093/</guid></item></channel></rss>